      "name": "In-vitro hemolysis index vs. CFD prediction — mean absolute error 12.1% across 6 operating points"
    }
  ],
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must hold ISO 9001 certification and pass all regression test suites relevant to turbulent rotating-machinery flows.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 holds ISO 9001 certification; internal regression suite passed 94% of rotating-machinery cases. One turbulence-model edge case failed; gap documented. Achieved level falls one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) must demonstrate second-order spatial convergence for all governing equations.",
      "rationale": "MMS applied to Navier-Stokes and species transport equations; second-order convergence confirmed for momentum but only 1.7-order achieved for scalar hemolysis transport equation. Gap acknowledged."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI must be below 5% for all quantities of interest on the finest mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed; GCI for velocity magnitude is 3.2% (meets criterion) but GCI for wall shear stress peaks at 7.8% in impeller tip region. Overall level constrained by wall shear stress gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions must be documented with uncertainty bounds and traceable to NIST-calibrated instruments.",
      "rationale": "All bench test boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, inlet pressure) measured with NIST-traceable instruments; expanded uncertainty U95 reported for each. Test conditions fully replicated in CFD setup."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g., E_avg) must be below 10% for primary QoI across all validation cases.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index E_avg = 12.1% across six operating points, exceeding the 10% threshold. Velocity field comparison meets criterion at 8.3%. Primary QoI (hemolysis) does not meet required threshold; level capped at 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must directly map to the clinical decision endpoint (hemolysis index for VAD patient safety).",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index (NIH normalized index of hemolysis) is the direct FDA-accepted clinical surrogate for red blood cell damage in VAD devices. QoI mapping is unambiguous and fully documented."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must cover the full operating envelope of the VAD COU including extreme flow and speed conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation data covers 3500–4000 RPM and 3.5–5.5 L/min; COU extends to 4500 RPM and 6 L/min. Upper operating envelope not validated experimentally. Extrapolation risk at boundary conditions reduces achieved level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals and round-off error contributions must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Solver convergence residuals monitored (L2 < 1e-6) but formal round-off error analysis not performed. Epistemic gap at MRL 5; factor flagged as not-assessed pending dedicated floating-point sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal user qualification records and simulation execution checklists must be on file demonstrating operator competency.",
      "rationale": "Analysts hold relevant CFD training certificates but formal user-error study (e.g., inter-analyst variability exercise) has not been conducted. Gap identified as epistemic at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic model-form uncertainty quantification must compare at least three turbulence model variants against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Only SST k-omega turbulence model used; RSM and LES comparisons planned but not completed. Model-form uncertainty unquantified. Epistemic gap at MRL 5 — factor not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated via Monte Carlo or equivalent method.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed for blood viscosity, inlet velocity profile, and rotational speed (±2%). Output variance attributed 61% to viscosity uncertainty. However, red blood cell mechanical properties (fragility index) not included in UQ sweep; partial gap remains."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood analog fluid characterization must include donor variability study with n ≥ 10 independent samples.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis experiments used porcine blood from a single lot. Human donor variability not characterized. Sample representativeness for Class III VAD patient population is unestablished. Epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency analysis must demonstrate that bench-test fluid properties match in-vivo blood rheology within defined tolerance bands.",
      "rationale": "Porcine blood viscosity at 37°C matched to human reference within 8% at 37.5 s-1 shear rate, but viscoelastic properties and hematocrit variability not formally mapped. Equivalency assessment incomplete at MRL 5."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-minimal-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The UnitOfAssurance is accepted under the Minimal profile. The claim that CFD can predict hemolysis index for the FDA generic centrifugal pump operating in VAD service conditions is supported by 7 of 13 assessed credibility factors meeting or approaching required levels at MRL 5. Six factors remain as documented epistemic gaps, consistent with an early-phase submission where iterative model maturation is expected. Monte Carlo UQ bounds the primary QoI uncertainty at ±18%. The decision team acknowledges that the intended use scope — Class III VAD pre-market submission support for adult end-stage heart failure patients at 2500–4500 RPM and 3–6 L/min — is described in the claim and requirement prose but has not been formally encoded as a structured Context of Use object. This gap is recorded for remediation prior to final regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
